Package com.complexible.common.memory

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Addressable
    Interface for an object which is stored off heap and accessible via its address in memory.
    ExtendedObjectSerializer<T>
    A small extension to ObjectSerializer which helps to serialize objects to ByteWriters and read from ByteReaders.
    FixedSizeObjectSerializer<T>
    An serializer which knows the size of all objects in advance.
    HashableObjectSerializer<T>
    An FixedSizeObjectSerializer which supports a native hasher for the objects which it serializes
    MemoryFlyweight
    Interface indicating that an object implements the flyweight pattern.
    MemoryManager.MemoryListener
    Listener interface that an object can implement in order to receive low-memory warnings from JMX
    MemoryPool
    A pool of memory from which allocations can occur.
    ObjectSerializer<T>
    A serializer which can round-trip POJOs to bytes for storage off heap or on disk.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractObjectSerializer<T>
    HashableObjectSerializerImpl<T>
    Memory
    Utility class around allocating memory via Unsafe
    MemoryPools
    Utilities for MemoryPool
    PrimitiveSerializers
    Serializers for Java primitives
    PrimitiveSerializers.LongSerializer  
    Reference
    Reference to an object stored off heap to facilitate flyweight access.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MemoryManager
    Memory management for the JVM.
    MemoryPool.Type  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NotEnoughMemoryException
    An exception to signal that a MemoryPool has been exhausted and cannot allocate any more memory.
